com.github.wuic

Class Context

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.wuic.Context
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Observer

    public class Context
extends Object
implements Observer

    The context is the core element of WUIC which allows to process nuts inside workflow.

    It is built thank to a ContextBuilder and is linked to it during it life cycles to know if the context is up to date regarding configuration changes since it has been built.

    Since:
    0.4.0
    Version:
    1.2
    Author:
    Guillaume DROUET

                     String wId,
                     String path,
                     UrlProviderFactory urlProviderFactory,
                     EngineType... skip)
                       throws WuicException

        Processes a workflow an returns the nut inside the result with a name that equals to the specified one.

        Parameters:
        skip - the skipped engine types
        contextPath - the context path where nuts will be referenced
        wId - the workflow ID
        path - the nut name
        urlProviderFactory - the URL provider
        Returns:
        the nut corresponding to the nut name
        Throws:
        WuicException - if workflow fails to be processed

      • isUpToDate

        public Boolean isUpToDate()

        Indicates if this context is up to date regarding the changes performed on the builder that built it.

        Returns:
        true if this context is up to date, false if the builder has been modified since the context has been generated
